# Changelog

All notable changes to Academia (docs + backend) are logged here, grouped by
development phase and date rather than semantic version, this project isn't
published as a versioned external release yet. Once the public API ships,
its endpoints will carry their own /v1/, /v2/ versioning independent of
this log.

This file is also published to the docs site as docs/changelog.md.

## [Unreleased]

## Docs Sync, 2026-07-04
### Changed
- api-contract.md: removed a stray "invalid status transition" error example
  from Update Question that didn't correspond to any documented request
  field; added a note that Question.status only changes as a side effect of
  answering, marking best, or deleting answers
- api-contract.md: documented that deleting an answer can revert Question
  status to ANSWERED (if the deleted answer was best and others remain) or
  OPEN (if it was the last remaining answer)
- api-contract.md: documented that marking a different answer as best
  transfers the flag rather than being blocked
- api-contract.md: added the previously undocumented List Comments endpoint
  (GET /answers/{answer_id}/comments/), closing a real gap where comments
  could be created but never retrieved anywhere
- feature-list.md: checkboxes updated to reflect actual implementation
  status through Phase 10 (previously reset to unchecked during an earlier
  sync as a fresh tracking baseline for this build)

### Process
- Folds in everything logged in BUILD_LOG.md's "Known Deviations" section
  across Phases 6 through 10

## Phase 10, Best Answer / Question Lifecycle, 2026-07-04
### Added
- Mark-best-answer endpoint, question-owner-only, transitions question to
  SOLVED, supports switching the best answer between answers on the same
  question
- Extended answer-delete logic: deleting the best answer while other
  answers remain now reverts status to ANSWERED, not just the "zero answers
  left reverts to OPEN" case from Phase 7
- List Comments endpoint (public, paginated), closing the gap noted above

## Phase 9, Comments, 2026-07-03
### Added
- Comment model (apps.comments), scoped to Answer
- Create (auth), update/delete (author-only)
- Answer.comment_count wired to real data

## Phase 8, Voting, 2026-07-03
### Added
- AnswerVote model (apps.answers)
- Vote/remove-vote endpoints, vote_score maintained via targeted F()
  updates to avoid race conditions under concurrent voting
- Self-voting and duplicate voting blocked (400, documented error shapes)

## Phase 7, Answers, 2026-07-03
### Added
- Answer model (apps.answers), create (auth, blocked on SOLVED questions),
  author-only edit/delete
- Question auto-transitions OPEN to ANSWERED on first answer
- Question.answer_count, best_answer_id, and nested answers array wired to
  real data
- Question status reverts to OPEN when its last remaining answer is deleted

### Deviated (resolved in Docs Sync, 2026-07-04)
- "Question is already SOLVED" error implemented as 400 Bad Request
  (field-keyed), not 403 Forbidden as api-contract.md labeled it at the
  time, matches the actual 400-shaped body already documented there

## Phase 6, Tags, 2026-07-03
### Added
- Tag and QuestionTag models (apps.tags)
- Tags normalized to lowercase and deduplicated on save
- Wired into question create/update/list/detail
- Tag list/search/popular endpoints, questions-by-tag endpoint, tag filter
  on the main question list

## Docs Sync, 2026-07-03
### Changed
- api-contract.md: documented the 404 response for GET /hubs/{hub_id}/
  (previously undocumented, implemented in Phase 4)
- api-contract.md: documented the error responses for POST
  /hubs/activation-requests/, duplicate pending request and
  already-active-hub cases (previously undocumented, implemented in Phase 4)
- api-contract.md: fixed a self-contradicting error label on POST
  /questions/, the invalid hub_id case was marked "404 Not Found" while
  showing a field-keyed 400 body; corrected to 400 Bad Request

### Process
- Folds in everything logged in BUILD_LOG.md's "Known Deviations" section
  across Phases 3 through 5

## Phase 5, Questions, 2026-07-03
### Added
- Question model (apps.questions), scoped to Hub with optional Department
- List (public, filterable by hub/department/status/search, orderable),
  create (auth), detail (public, increments view_count), update/delete
  (author-only), unanswered queue (admin-only for now)
- Hub.question_count and Department.question_count wired to real data

## Phase 4, Hubs + Activation Requests, 2026-07-02
### Added
- Hub + HubActivationRequest models (apps.hubs)
- GET /hubs/{hub_id}/ and GET /hubs/by-school/{school_id}/ (public)
- Activation request create (auth) / list (admin, status filter) / approve
  (admin, creates the Hub) / reject (admin)
- School.has_hub and the has_hub list filter wired to real data, replacing
  the Phase 2 stub

### Deviated (resolved in Docs Sync, 2026-07-03)
- Activation request creation blocks duplicate PENDING requests and
  requests against schools with an already-active hub, not documented in
  api-contract.md at the time
- GET /hubs/{hub_id}/ 404 error body was assumed, not explicitly
  documented at the time

## Phase 3, Departments, 2026-07-02
### Added
- Department model added to apps.schools
- List (public) + create (admin-only) scoped under
  /schools/{id}/departments/; update (admin-only) at /departments/{id}/
- Soft-delete via is_active, same pattern as School

## Docs Sync, 2026-07-02
### Changed
- database-schema.md, api-contract.md, project-plan.md, feature-list.md
  updated to reflect everything logged across Phases 0 through 2
- Added verification_status to School; documented soft-delete via PATCH
- Converted Report/Notification to Django's ContentType framework
  internally; public JSON shape unchanged
- Added APIClient model and Future Models section (SchoolReview,
  ReviewCategoryScore, ReviewResponse, ReviewVote, Plan, Subscription,
  Invoice, SchoolSubmission) to database-schema.md
- Added versioning policy and a full step-by-step "How Google Auth Works"
  frontend implementation guide to api-contract.md
- Added "Integrity Over Monetization" principle, API/public-API strategy,
  future Reviews and Monetization sections, and a Developer Tooling and
  Data Sourcing backlog note to project-plan.md
- Added Future Features to feature-list.md
- Introduced this CHANGELOG.md and its docs-site counterpart

### Process
- Established the doc-maintenance system: BUILD_LOG.md tracks short-term
  phase-by-phase state; the four core docs are updated in periodic sync
  passes; this CHANGELOG carries the durable history

## Phase 2, Schools, 2026-07-01
### Added
- School model (apps.schools), list/search/detail endpoints (public read)
- Admin-only create/update via IsPlatformAdmin permission
- Global error-response normalizer (apps.core.exceptions)

### Deviated (resolved in Docs Sync, 2026-07-02)
- api-contract.md didn't document a School delete endpoint; resolved via
  soft-delete (is_active=False) through the existing PATCH endpoint
- database-schema.md's School model gained verification_status

## Phase 1, Auth, 2026-07-01
### Added
- Custom User model (UUID PK, email-based, apps.accounts)
- Google OAuth login, JWT issuance (SimpleJWT, refresh rotation and
  blacklist)
- Endpoints: /api/v1/auth/google/, /api/v1/auth/refresh/,
  /api/v1/auth/logout/, /api/v1/users/me/ (GET/PATCH)

### Deviated (resolved in Docs Sync, 2026-07-02)
- project-plan.md named django-allauth for social auth; implemented instead
  via direct verification against Google's userinfo endpoint
- database-schema.md's User model didn't list is_staff; added for Django
  admin-site compatibility, kept separate from is_admin

## Phase 0, Scaffolding, 2026-07-01
### Added
- Django 6.0.6 project scaffold, split settings
  (base/development/production)
- PostgreSQL connection via django-environ
- Health-check endpoint at /api/v1/health/
